  📝 Retrieved Answer:
  ----------------------------------------------------------
  The goals of Online Transaction Processing (OLTP) and data analytics are fundamentally different. OLTP is designed to handle high-volume, real-time transactions, ensuring that the system can process and respond to a large number of requests quickly and accurately. The primary goal is to provide a seamless and efficient experience for users, minimizing response times and ensuring data integrity.
  
  On the other hand, data analytics aims to extract insights and knowledge from large datasets. It involves analyzing historical data to identify patterns, trends, and correlations that can be used to make informed decisions. The goal is to provide actionable information that can be used to improve business operations, drive strategic decisions, and enhance customer experiences.
  
  In summary, OLTP focuses on real-time processing and transactional accuracy, while data analytics emphasizes the analysis of historical data to derive meaningful insights.
  ----------------------------------------------------------

